quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  7,48,"And they who are upon Al Araf shall cry to those whom they shall know by their tokens, \"Your amassings and your pride have availed you nothing"
  7,49,"Are these they on whom ye sware God would not bestow mercy? Enter ye into Paradise! where no fear shall be upon you, neither shall ye be put to grief"
  7,50,"And the inmates of the fire shall cry to the inmates of Paradise: \"Pour upon us some water, or of the refreshments God hath given you?\" They shall say, \"Truly God hath forbidden both to unbelievers"
  7,51,"Who made their religion a sport and pastime, and whom the life of the world hath deceived.\" This day therefore will we forget them, as they forgot the meeting of this their day, and as they did deny our signs"
  7,52,"And now have we brought them the Book: with knowledge have we explained it; a guidance and a mercy to them that believe"
  7,53,"What have they to wait for now but its interpretation? When its interpretation shall come, they who aforetime were oblivious of it shall say, \"The Prophets of our Lord did indeed bring the truth; shall we have any intercessor to intercede for us? or could we not be sent back? Then would we act otherwise than we have acted.\" But they have ruined themselves; and the deities of their own devising have fled from them"